  "text": "containing paths with at least one occurrence of the n-gram w. These posterior probabilities are used in MBR decoding under the linear approximation to the BLEU score described in [CITATION_1] . We find that for system combination, decoding often produces output that is slightly shorter than required. A fixed per-word factor optimized on the tuning set is applied when computing the gain and this results in output with improved BLEU score and reduced brevity penalty. Table 7 shows translation results in Arabic-to-English using three alternative morphological decompositions of the Arabic text (upper rows a, b, and c). For each decomposition an independent set of hierarchical rules is obtained from the respective parallel corpus alignments. The decompositions were generated by the MADA toolkit [CITATION_2] with two alternative tokenization schemes, and by the Sakhr Arabic Morphological Tagger, developed by Sakhr Software in Egypt.",
